video_title: Trading 101: Your First Step Into Financial Markets [Beginner‚Äôs Guide 2025] | 9xMarkets
video_description:
New to financial trading and not sure where to start? This beginner-friendly class gives you a solid foundation without jargon or hype. You‚Äôll learn how markets are structured, what different instruments mean in practice, how order types work, and why risk control matters more than any single strategy. We walk through the essentials of using a trading platform, interpreting quotes and spreads, calculating position size with leverage and margin, and building a simple, repeatable routine for your first month. The goal is clarity: understand how decisions turn into trades, how costs impact results, and how to protect yourself from common beginner mistakes.

We start with the big picture: what moves forex, indices, commodities, and crypto CFDs, and how liquidity and sessions affect price behavior. You‚Äôll see how brokers, liquidity providers, and pricing streams interact, so you can set realistic expectations about execution, slippage, and swaps. Next, we simplify order types‚Äîmarket, limit, and stop‚Äîand show where each makes sense. You‚Äôll practice thinking in risk units (R), so one losing trade never derails your plan. We‚Äôll also cover the difference between spread-only and commission models, how to read the contract specifications for an instrument, and what changes when volatility expands.

To make it practical, we include a day-one setup checklist: creating a clean watchlist, choosing two or three instruments to focus on, turning on two-factor authentication, and setting platform defaults (lot step, one-click trading, confirmations). We outline a compact pre-trade routine‚Äîidentify the session, note key levels, define invalidation, pre-calculate stop distance, convert it into position size, and only then place the order. After entry, you‚Äôll learn how to monitor margin level, track unrealized P/L, and manage exits without second-guessing every tick. A simple post-trade journal template helps you capture entry rationale, risk taken, result vs. plan, and one improvement for the next trade.

Common pitfalls are addressed head-on: over-sizing positions, chasing news candles, trading too many pairs, moving stops, revenge trading, and ignoring swap/financing costs. You‚Äôll learn a lightweight approach to drawdown control‚Äîhard daily loss limit, weekly circuit-breaker, and how to scale down size during losing streaks. Finally, we map out a 30-day practice plan: weeks one and two on execution basics, week three on consistency and journaling, week four on refining your edge and creating a checklist you‚Äôll actually use.

You‚Äôll learn
‚Ä¢ Market structure, instruments, and sessions in plain language
‚Ä¢ Platform basics: symbols, order tickets, stop/limit usage, P/L and margin
‚Ä¢ Position sizing by risk amount rather than ‚Äúlots that feel right‚Äù
‚Ä¢ A simple trade lifecycle: prepare, place, manage, review
‚Ä¢ A month-one routine that builds skill without burning capital

Who this is for
Absolute beginners, explorers switching brokers, and anyone who wants a clear, rules-based start focused on risk and repeatability rather than shortcuts.

Mini-exercises
‚Ä¢ Convert a fixed money risk into lot size for three instruments
‚Ä¢ Write a one-sentence trade thesis before every entry
‚Ä¢ Define your daily max loss and stick to it for two weeks
‚Ä¢ Journal five trades and identify a single recurring improvement

Common mistakes we fix
Oversized leverage, trading every alert, confusing market vs. pending orders, ignoring swaps, skipping the journal, and adding to losing trades.

FAQs

Do I need a strategy before I start?
You need a basic framework first: risk per trade, when you‚Äôll enter/exit, and what invalidates a trade. A simple approach beats a complex one you won‚Äôt follow.

How much capital do I need?
Enough to apply your chosen risk per trade without rounding errors. Focus on percentage/risk-unit thinking; consistency matters more than account size at the start.

Is leverage good or bad?
Leverage is a tool; misuse makes losses faster. Keep per-trade risk small and margin levels healthy, and you‚Äôll neutralize most leverage risks.

Why am I stopped out quickly?
Stops are often set inside market noise. Base stop distance on structure/volatility, then size your position to fit your risk amount.

How do I avoid overtrading?
Limit instruments, predefine setups, cap daily trades, and require a written thesis before clicking buy/sell.

Risk Warning: CFDs are complex instruments and come with a high risk of losing money rapidly due to leverage. Educational content only; not financial advice.

video_title: How to use the UVA 2 Menstrual Cup
video_description:
Step 1
Sterilize
You should always sterilize your UVA menstrual cup at the beginning and end of your menstrual cycle. There are two ways to do this:

Insert the UVA 2 menstrual cup into the sterilizer and cover it completely with water. Then, microwave it for 3 to 4 minutes, being sure not to completely close the lid. Afterward, carefully remove the water and let the cup cool before using it.

Put your cup in the sterilizer and cover it with boiling water, place the lid and let it sit for 5 minutes. Let it cool before using it.

Step 2
Insert
Wash your hands and adopt a comfortable position, whether in the shower or on the toilet. With practice, you will learn which position is best for you. Choose the most comfortable fold for you. Here are some examples:

While holding the cup folded in one hand, use the other hand to insert it with the rim facing up. Once it's completely inside, press the bottom of the cup with your index finger and thumb to create a vacuum effect. It will open up inside your vaginal canal and fit perfectly to your body.

Step 3
Check
Take it by the pull tab and give it a little twist. If you feel any discomfort or folds, remove it and try again until you feel comfortable with it.

Step 4
Remove
Before removing the cup, wash your hands thoroughly. Take a comfortable position again and insert your fingers to press the bottom of the cup to release the vacuum effect. Relax your pelvic floor (as if you were going to pee) and carefully remove it.

Step 5
Clean
Empty the menstrual cup, at least every 12 hours, by depositing the contents in the toilet. Rinse with water, apply UVA cleaner, and rinse again. Remember that at the end of your menstrual cycle, you should repeat step number 1, sterilization.

Step 6
Store your cup and sterilizer in a cool, dry place where they are not exposed to direct sunlight. Use the cotton bag included in your purchase to keep them protected.

video_title: Peace Engineering: A Partnered Approach to Engineering Education and Research
video_description:
The increasing impacts of climate change, urbanization, population growth and migration, along with the rapid adoption of technology in our day-to-day lives will continue to create conflict within and among communities; when systems lack the resiliency necessary to dampen this conflict, the outcome is often violence. Knowing that technological design has the ability to both contribute to or mitigate violence, future community leaders will be increasingly involved in all stages of conflict progression, and ultimately in the outcome of either peace or violence. Additionally, engineers will be increasingly involved in guiding the implementation and use of their work. We will explore the role of universities in community partnership and identify skill sets and best practices that will guide the emerging field of peace engineering. 

Dr. Mira Olson is an Associate Professor in the Departments of Civil, Architectural and Environmental Engineering and Engineering, Leadership and Society at Drexel University. She holds a B.S in Mechanical Engineering and B.A. in Environmental Sciences and Engineering from Rice University, and an M.E. and Ph.D. in Civil (Environmental) Engineering from the University of Virginia. The broad focus of her research is on protecting source water quality, with current interests in transboundary water management and community-based research design. Dr. Olson‚Äôs research has been funded by the National Science Foundation (NSF), the U.S. Environmental Protection Agency (USEPA), the Water Environment Research Foundation (WERF), the United States Geological Survey (USGS), the United States Department of Agriculture (USDA), as well as local utilities and foundations. Dr. Olson is a past editor of the International Journal of Engineering, Social Justice and Peace, is trained in community-based learning and currently serves as faculty fellow in Drexel‚Äôs Office of University and Community Partnerships. She directs Drexel‚Äôs newly established Peace Engineering program. 

Discussant Keil Eggers is a Ph.D. candidate and Peace Engineering Fellow at the Jimmy and Rosalynn Carter School for Peace and Conflict Resolution. He holds an M.A. of International Peace Studies from the UN-Mandated University for Peace. At the Carter School Peace Engineering Lab, he focuses on developing scalable intervention strategies to conflict powered by a narrative sense-making technology called SenseMaker. In his dissertation research titled ‚ÄúUs Against When: The Futures of Complexity-Informed Conflict Transformation in the United States,‚Äù he has adapted SenseMaker methodology to explore interpretations of future artifacts generated by prominent U.S.-based peacebuilding organizations in order to make interventions in states at risk for political violence more meaningful, scalable, and successful.

The webinar is hosted by Dr. Caitlin Wylie, Associate Professor of Science, Technology, and Society at UVA‚Äôs School of Engineering and Applied Sciences.

‚ÄúMarble Run‚Äù

üìå Inside or Outside game
üìå Shooting accuracy, speed, balance
üìå Great for ages 3+

Equipment required:
üéØ 1 x ramp material (construction of your own choosing) cardboard, timber, cushions
üéØ Materials to create incline for ramp - paint tins, stools, cushions, pillows etc
üéØ Multiple buckets (min 3) - baskets, bins or similar work well
üéØ 2 x tennis balls or similar. More balls the better
üéØ Min 1 participant but can add as many as you wish

Instructions: 
‚úÖ Create a flat ramp using an open flat cardboard box (preferred). Ensure the ramp has incline using materials underneath and has a finished height higher than the buckets
‚úÖ Place buckets at end of ramp at different distances away form end of ramp 
‚úÖ Determine a points system for successful attempts into buckets/baskets. For eg - bucket 1 = 10pts, bucket 2 = 20 pts, bucket 3 = 30pts, bucket 4 = 100 pts.
** Note - we added increased pts for the furthest bucket as it presents the greatest challenge and most likely for ball to fall off the ramp
‚úÖ Players take turn shooting tennis balls up ramp. They add points for successful buckets

Variations:
üí° Try shooting with non-preferred hand
üí° Add ‚Äòtrick shots‚Äô such as through the legs, behind the back or facing the wrong way
üí° Add full body rotations prior to shooting - don‚Äôt fall over!

video_title: About GCM: A central hub of insights for Community Managers
video_description:
After years of working in the gaming industry and helping community managers bring together, moderate, and engage their players on a higher level, we came to a somewhat troubling realization.
While there are resources galore for marketers, designers, and business managers, the gaming industry is void of a go-to hub for community managers to gather and share information on their vital trade.

That's where GCM Hub came into being.

By crafting industry-focused articles, podcasts, and other informational materials, we hope to provide you with the best resources out there and set you on the path to stepping up your community management game.

GCM Hub is here to help you learn from and become exactly that: the best.

Thanks for watching, we hope you enjoyed the video! Don't forget to share, like and subscribe.

ABOUT GAME:

This offroad 4x4 game contains American and German cars is an outstanding environment(muddy forest). You can drive alone in offline mode or just drive among others drivers in online ( multiplayer ) mode. 

This off-road multiplayer jeep car game has 4x4 SUV cars like Predator, Hammer, Jeep, Q7, X6, Range, Wrangler, Rover. These cars are petrol and diesel ones. The torque of this cars will help you to climb the rocks, to pass through the mud and jump over the hills.

After you buy the 4x4 you want, you can customize it with wheels( this game has over 30 sets of wheels ). Also, you can paint the car in which color you want from the game color pallet. The car torque, brake, transmission,  steering power, nitro( nos ) and speed can be customized with a tuning soft in the game garage.

If you are ready to drive outlaw in wild forest, download this off-road game today.

- Outstanding graphics
- 5 offroad cars (we add new cars)
- Online and offline mode ( multiplayer )
- 30 wheels sets
- brake, transmission 4x4,  torque and steering power tuning system.
- Mud forest with a river.
- Car color exchange
- US cars
- Rock crawler
- Free to play

https://preview.drivethrurpg.com/en/product/537/lair-of-the-hidden

I hope you find this creature as fascinating as I did. 
Enjoy!

video_title: PMA¬Æ Tensile Test, according to ISO 527-1/2
video_description: Intensive testing, research and development activity is a top priority at PMA¬Æ every day. That's why ABB‚Äôs PMA¬Æ Cable Protection is a market leader in the field of cable protection. The ISO 527-1/2 standard specifies a method for determining the tensile properties of plastic materials. This test is conducted using a universal testing machine, where standardized specimens are subjected to uniaxial tensile stress under controlled conditions until failure. The primary goal is to generate a stress-strain curve that characterizes the mechanical behavior of the material. This standard is essential for R&D in polymer engineering and material development, providing reliable data on the strength, stiffness, and ductility of polymer materials.

video_title: StarRupture: Where even the Sun wants you Dead
video_description:
Welcome to a short video showcasing the power of StarRupture's sun, introducing the game's basic concept, and my initial thoughts on it.

StarRupture is an automation and exploration game with survival elements, where you, the player, and any optional friends are convicts attempting to work out your sentence by extracting resources and sending them back to corporations on Earth. You're not the first group to arrive here, and those that came before you on Arcadia are already dead.

Can you succeed where they failed, or will the planet's very own Sun incinerate any hope of freedom and redemption?

Let me know what you think, and I look forward to your feedback on making additional videos of this upcoming game!

video_title: Eagan police concluded high school band teacher, Brett Benson, groomed students
video_description:
An investigation into Eagan High School music teacher Brett David Benson was opened in 2022 after the Rosemount-Apple Valley-Eagan district contacted police on a report that Benson, then age 35, allegedly sneaked a student out of her room during a school trip to Italy.

Eagan police detective Chad Clausen eventually interviewed more than 40 people, including teachers, parents and Benson‚Äôs former students. He also spoke to Benson, who denied any wrongdoing.

Elizabeth Shockman reports that what Clausen concluded, according to his 100-page investigative report completed in 2023, went much deeper than a single allegation on a school trip.

Hannah LoPresto and Sophie Panetti were two of the students who spoke to Clausen for his investigation. They agreed to speak to MPR News on the record.

Story by Elizabeth Shockman, video by Anne Guttridge
